  "text": "In first, \"naive server\", all data is sent from the server, but all clients are ON for the entire duration. The second, \"naive P2P\", is the P2P scheme [CITATION_1] that minimizes the total download time of all peers, which again requires that all peers be ON during the download. In \"Opt server\", all data is sent from the server, but peers are either OFF or being uploaded to at full rate D i . \"Opt P2P\" is the scheme of Section III.",
